    <statement><p>Simplify this expression, and if applicable, write the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{8x-32}{-10-15x-5x^{2}}} \cdot {\frac{x^{2}+4x+4}{2x^{2}-8x}} =}</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>-\frac{4\mathopen{}\left(x+2\right)}{5x\mathopen{}\left(x+1\right)}, x\ne 4\hbox{ and }x\ne -2</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{8x-32}{-10-15x-5x^{2}}} \cdot {\frac{x^{2}+4x+4}{2x^{2}-8x}} 
      \amp = \frac{{8x-32}}{-5x^2-15x - 10} \cdot {\frac{x^{2}+4x+4}{2x^{2}-8x}} \\
      \amp = \frac{{8\mathopen{}\left(x-4\right)}}{{-5\mathopen{}\left(x^{2}+3x+2\right)}} \cdot \frac{{\left(x+2\right)^{2}}}{{2x\mathopen{}\left(x-4\right)}} \\
      \amp = \frac{{8\mathopen{}\left(x-4\right)}}{{-5\mathopen{}\left(x+2\right)\mathopen{}\left(x+1\right)}} \cdot \frac{{\left(x+2\right)^{2}}}{{2x\mathopen{}\left(x-4\right)}} \\
      \amp = {-\frac{4\mathopen{}\left(x+2\right)}{5x\mathopen{}\left(x+1\right)}, x\ne 4\hbox{ and }x\ne -2}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factors <m>x-4</m> and <m>x + 2</m> were canceled, the domain condition lost during the simplification is <m>x \ne {4, -2}</m>.</p>
</solution>
